DESCRIPTION:Sail the scenic waterway on a 90-minute\, guided tour from down
	town to Waugh Drive Bridge and back to watch the emergence of the 250\,000
	+ Mexican free-tailed bats that live under the bridge. \nOur knowledgeable
	 guide will share details about the bats’ eating patterns\, behavior and c
	ontributions to the bayou’s ecosystem. Space is limited\, and boat tours f
	ill up fast. Boat departs 45 minutes before sunset. \nCost\nStarting at $3
	0/person \nDuration\n90 minutes \nDeparture location\n Allen’s Landing (10
	19 Commerce St.) \nPlease note\, children must be at least four years old 
	to board the pontoon boat. \n  \nPURCHASE TICKETS\n\nhttps://buffalobayou.
	org/event/2026-june-buffalo-bayou-cruise-bats-30-3/\n\nFrom Buffalo Bayou 
	Partnership
URL:https://buffalobayou.org/event/2026-june-buffalo-bayou-cruise-bats-30-3
	/
LOCATION:ALLEN’S LANDING\, 1001 Commerce Street\, Houston\, TX\, 77002\, Un
	ited States
